title: Previously Unseen Footage - Buddy Rich Tells Mel Torme about Artie Shaw & Mexico
description:
30% Off All Drum Channel Memberships! (exp. 12/1) ➜ https://drmch.nl/2ZiKWpS


Celebrate Back To School season with 30% off all Drum Channel memberships, for a limited time only!
➡️ https://drmch.nl/2YdoMoe ⬅️
Legendary drummer Buddy Rich interviews his good friend, "The Velvet Fog," Mel Torme on the set of "The Buddy Rich Show in 1982. This previously unseen clip is from three lost pilot episodes of "The Buddy Rich Show."

Drumming educational website, Drumchannel is raising money for the licensing fees to finally release these three previously unseen pilot tv shows on DVD. The three shows recorded in 1982 at the Statler Hotel in NYC also feature interviews, outtakes and performances from The Buddy Rich band along with jazz and big band greats Ray Charles, Lionel Hampton, Woody Herman, Stan Getz and Gerry Mulligan. Check out the great perks and help us make this happen! This is a dream almost 40 years in the making!
